modern_classics.title: Modern Classics
modern_classics.description: Your desert-island movies are definitely in here.

229885.title: Night of the Living Dead
229885.description: A group of strangers struggles to fend off an attack of bloodthirsty zombies while barricading themselves inside a rural Pennsylvania farmhouse.

255766.title: The Kentucky Fried Movie
255766.description: A wide array of hilarious short skits aim to mercilessly spoof and skewer almost every film genre, from blaxploitation to infomercials.

268891.title: Aguirre: The Wrath of God
268891.description: In the 16th century, the ruthless and insane Don Lope de Aguirre leads a Spanish expedition in search of El Dorado.

269877.title: Fitzcarraldo
269877.description: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

279411.title: Hoop Dreams
279411.description: One of the highest grossing documentaries in United States history, this multi-award-winning, Oscar-nominated film tells the inspiring true story of Chicago students who dream of becoming pro basketball players.

283631.title: Assault on Precinct 13
283631.description: In this action thriller, an understaffed police station enlists the help of criminals when they become a target of a deadly street gang.

294101.title: Election
294101.description: In this thrilling Hong Kong action film, every two years the senior members of the Triads elect a new chairman, and nothing will stop rival leaders from using any means necessary to gain power.

294112.title: Triad Election
294112.description: Famed Hong Kong director Johnnie To helms this stylish crime thriller about plotting and wrestling for power in the streets and boardrooms of Hong Kong.

300446.title: The Birdcage
300446.description: In this colorful comedy classic, a gay cabaret owner (Robin Williams) and his drag queen partner (Nathan Lane) agree to pass themselves off as a straight couple so that their son can introduce them to his fiancée's right-wing, moralistic parents (Gene Hackman and Dianne Wiest).

300449.title: Eight Men Out
300449.description: A dramatization about the infamous 1919 "Black Sox Scandal," in which eight members of the Chicago White Sox conspired with gamblers to throw the World Series in return for cash.

300451.title: It's A Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad World
300451.description: A multitude of people have been given a clue by a dying man as to the location of $350,000 in stolen bank money that he has buried and set out separately in a mad race to get to it first.

300454.title: Moonstruck
300454.description: Loretta Castorini (Cher), a bookkeeper from Brooklyn, New York, finds herself in a difficult situation when she falls for the brother of the man she has agreed to marry.

300463.title: Return of the Pink Panther
300463.description: Dispatched to a Swiss resort town, Clouseau must investigate cat-burglar Sir Charles and his wife Claudine through a series of hilarious disguises.

300465.title: Rob Roy
300465.description: In eighteenth century Scotland, a cattle farmer, who cannot repay his debt to the aristocratic Marquis of Montrose, fights for his integrity.

301154.title: Nutcracker
301154.description: In this holiday classic, a young woman is whisked away to an enchanted land of dolls and a dangerous mouse king when her toy nutcracker comes to life.

301237.title: The Purple Rose Of Cairo
301237.description: A comedy-fantasy about a Depression-era movie fan/waitress whose day-to-day existence is enlivened when her latest idol walks right off the screen and into her life!

302153.title: The Cutting Edge
302153.description: After suffering a career-ending head injury, a talented hockey player trains with a difficult figure skater to compete in the 1992 Winter Olympics.

302158.title: Eat Drink Man Woman
302158.description: In this comedy-drama, Taiwan's most famous chef has lost his wife and his sense of taste. Now, he's losing the innocence of his daughters.

302163.title: Rosencrantz And Guildenstern Are Dead
302163.description: The filmization of Tom Stoppard's immensely witty Shakespearean spin-off, which changes the tone of "Hamlet" from a tragedy to a comedy. Adventures of Rosencrantz and Guildenstern, two lesser characters from Hamlet, as they romp around the castle.

302693.title: Koyaanisqatsi
302693.description: A motion picture essay which takes a revealing and shocking look at modern life and its imbalances.  The first film in a trilogy which was followed by Powaqatsi.

302695.title: Last Tango In Paris
302695.description: A man, torn apart by his wife's suicide, attempts to bury his grief in a sudden, purely carnal relationship with an alluring, young stranger.

302703.title: Lenny
302703.description: Based on the true story, Lenny Bruce finds himself with more fans and an obscenity charge when he seeks to perform groundbreaking, edgier comedy.

302708.title: The Long Goodbye
302708.description: In this neo-noir thriller, a private detective is determined to solve a difficult case after he becomes a suspect in the murder of his friend’s wife.

302723.title: The Night Of The Hunter
302723.description: Robert Mitchum stars in an unforgettable role as a psychopathic preacher in relentless pursuit of two children who have their dead father's stolen fortune hidden in a doll.  Shelley Winters co-stars.

303018.title: The Wedding Banquet
303018.description: A gay man plans a sham marriage to appease his traditional Taiwanese parents in this modern comedy but creates a rift with his real boyfriend.

303080.title: Henry V
303080.description: In the midst of the Hundred Years War, a young and uncertain King Henry V defeats the French but learns that victory takes its toll in bloodshed.

303190.title: The Usual Suspects
303190.description: The lone survivor of a heist-gone-wrong tells the feds how it all went down as they search for the enigmatic crime lord behind the disaster.

304768.title: An American Werewolf In London
304768.description: In this '80s horror comedy classic, David Kessler and Jack Goodman arrive in Northern England for a walking tour. One night, a beast attacks them, killing Jack. Weeks later Jack returns to warn David that a werewolf was their assailant, and that he is now the last of the their kind!

304773.title: Drugstore Cowboy
304773.description: Bob leads a family of junkies that rob drug stores for their fix. When a member dies, he goes straight. But not everyone is willing to let him leave.

304803.title: Hair
304803.description: With exuberance, inventiveness and humor, Treat Williams and Beverly D'Angelo lead a cast of future stars in this film of one of Broadway's most popular musical phenomenons of all time.

304810.title: Thunderbolt and Lightfoot
304810.description: While fleeing from a theft, a drifter meets a legendary criminal who's also on the run. The duo reunite with their old partners to plan a bank heist.

305011.title: Cutter's Way
305011.description: This intriguing film features John Heard as a boozy, belligerent Vietnam vet who seeks passionate revenge on a murderer after his aimless friend (Jeff Bridges) is falsely accused of the crime.

305029.title: UHF
305029.description: The manager of a small-time UHF station inadvertently hits it big with his strange programming ideas to keep Channel 62 from going down the tubes.

305811.title: Elmer Gantry
305811.description: A charming conman pretends to be a preacher and romances a roadside revivalist. Will his charade collapse when an ex-lover shows up to settle a score?

305835.title: Rollerball
305835.description: James Caan stars as a rollerball champ in this fast-hitting, action- packed glimpse of a future where a brutal, no-holds-barred sport takes the place of war, and murder is just part of the game.

305868.title: Kes
305868.description: Director Ken Loach received international acclaim for this enormously moving tale of a lonely working-class Yorkshire boy, who turns from a life of comic books and shoplifting when he finds a baby kestrel and decides to raise and train it.

305872.title: The Missouri Breaks
305872.description: This is the rousing story of a wealthy Montana rancher who hires a professional killer to track down a gang of horse thieves.

306922.title: Buffalo Bill And The Indians
306922.description: To add some spectacle to his expolitative and inaccurate Wild West show, Buffalo Bill hires Sitting Bull, who becomes an accidental star.

306940.title: The Pink Panther Strikes Again
306940.description: After escaping from an insane asylum, the hilariously crazy Chief Inspector Dreyfus (Herbert Lom) sends 26 assassins on the trail of hapless Inspector Closeau (Peter Sellers).

307212.title: Trees Lounge
307212.description: Tommy is an unemployed mechanic who spends most of his time in a bar in a small, blue collar town. He seems to always be thinking, "If only X then I could stop drinking".

310149.title: The Secret of NIMH
310149.description: In this animated adventure, a timid mouse seeks help from a colony of intelligent rats to save her family, but the rats have their own problems.

310154.title: 12 Angry Men
310154.description: A twelve-person jury becomes increasingly tense with arguments continuing into the night as one juror must convince the other eleven he is right.

312175.title: Dirty Rotten Scoundrels
312175.description: Who will emerge as the ultimate hustler when a sophisticated con man and a free-wheeling huckster compete to scam an heiress out of $50,000?

312178.title: Foxy Brown
312178.description: After her brother betrays her, a woman goes undercover as a prostitute in order to find the gangsters who killed her boyfriend — and get revenge.

312179.title: Get Shorty
312179.description: A gangster goes to Hollywood to collect a debt and becomes a big-time producer when he realizes the movie business runs a lot like the mob.

312184.title: The Last Waltz
312184.description: This classic concert documentary focuses on The Band’s farewell concert in San Francisco, where they are joined by a number of special musical guests.

312187.title: Midnight Cowboy
312187.description: This Academy Award-winning Best Picture features Dustin Hoffman and Jon Voight in standout roles as a con man and a Texas hustler trying to survive on the tough streets of New York.

312196.title: Showgirls
312196.description: An aspiring Las Vegas showgirl works as a stripper in order to claw her way up in the world, using sex and seduction to get what she wants.

312409.title: The Apartment
312409.description: A corporate drone hatches a scheme for success: Let the execs use his apartment for “dates.” It goes beautifully, until his love interest gets hurt.

312417.title: Hoosiers
312417.description: A man gets a last chance at redemption by coaching a small-town Indiana high-school basketball team and bring his team to the 1951 state championship.

316454.title: Secretary
316454.description: Hoping to recover from her troubled past, a socially awkward woman becomes a secretary for an eccentric lawyer who is aroused by her obedience.

316463.title: Rabbit Hole
316463.description: A married couple grieves the loss of their young son. Director John Cameron Mitchell brings a restrained hand to this moving film.

321122.title: Hercules in New York
321122.description: When Zeus banishes Hercules to Earth, he decides to amuse himself by becoming a bodybuilder, but he struggles to adapt to life in New York City.

326260.title: Suspiria
326260.description: A series of gruesome murders and inexplicable events lead a new student to suspect something evil is at play at a prestigious ballet academy.

334156.title: Mad Max
334156.description: A vengeful cop and a sadistic motorcycle gang face off in a chaotic wasteland.

334159.title: The Return of the Living Dead
334159.description: While working at a medical supply company, two employees release a gas that raises the dead, causing the town to be overrun with flesh-eating zombies.

355681.title: The Amityville Horror
355681.description: The middle-class Lutz family are terrorized by their new Long Island home...which is possessed by demons.

356528.title: Bowling for Columbine
356528.description: This documentary examines gun violence in the U.S. in relation to other countries, including the specific events that led to the Columbine massacre.

356529.title: A Fish Called Wanda
356529.description: After pulling off a diamond heist, the motley crew of culprits dupe one another repeatedly in hopes of pocketing the loot, in this black comedy.

358575.title: Mississippi Burning
358575.description: Based on the true story, two FBI agents investigate the disappearance of three Mississippi civil rights activists in 1964.

389503.title: Robocop
389503.description: A cop who died in the line of duty is transformed into a chrome-plated cyborg policeman with an indestructible new body and a thirst for revenge.

393462.title: Grizzly Man
393462.description: A compelling documentary look at the life and death of wildlife preservationist Timothy Treadwell, who lived unarmed among grizzly bears in Alaska.

394492.title: Ghost World
394492.description: Based on the well-known comic,  two high school students taking a hard look at the world they wryly observe and decide what they really want, altering their friendship forever.

399691.title: Requiem for a Dream
399691.description: The lives of four people intertwine in this gut-wrenching, hypnotic tale of addiction and the devastation it has on their lives and those around them.

404623.title: Battle Royale
404623.description: A group of students from a Japanese high school are forced to compete in a battle, killing one another until only one is left standing.

405675.title: Thief
405675.description: A master safecracker plans his last heist for the sake of a woman but the gangster who hires him won't let go so easily in this tense drama.

448255.title: Bad Lieutenant
448255.description: A corrupt New York City cop seeks redemption while investigating the rape of a young nun and battling the addictions that drive him toward insanity.

448257.title: Amores Perros
448257.description: A horrific car accident connects the lives of three strangers: a lovesick dog fighter, an injured supermodel and a hitman running from his past.

448663.title: Leaving Las Vegas
448663.description: Determined to end it all, a committed drinker picks Vegas as his last stop, but he finds comfort with a kind prostitute who needs help of her own.

448987.title: Last House on the Left
448987.description: Two girls are tortured and left to die after they become captives of four prison escapees who end up facing off with one of the girls' mothers.

460204.title: King of New York
460204.description: A New York drug lord just released from prison is determined to rule the streets again with a vengeance in this gritty action film.

463715.title: On Golden Pond
463715.description: At Golden Pond, a couple agree to care of Billy, the son of their daughter Chelsea's new boyfriend, and a most unexpected relationship blooms.

463838.title: The Last Unicorn
463838.description: A brave unicorn and a magician fight an evil king who is obsessed with attempting to capture the world's unicorns.

465154.title: Slumber Party Massacre
465154.description: In this cult horror classic, a maniac on the loose takes his weapon of choice, a huge power drill, to a gathering of unsuspecting young women.

465237.title: Sophie's Choice
465237.description: Not long after World War II, a novelist grows close to a mysterious woman who survived the Holocaust, but her secrets reveal an even deeper tragedy.

466262.title: Something Wild
466262.description: When a conservative businessman accepts a ride from a free-spirited woman, she takes him on an outrageous ride that veers between fun and danger.

466619.title: Married to the Mob
466619.description: Living a normal life isn't easy for a mobster's widow when she attracts the attention of an enamored FBI agent and a married Mafioso.

466939.title: Cockfighter
466939.description: A gritty cockfighting veteran, after losing his shot at victory, vows to remain silent until one of his birds wins the championship.

469586.title: Hard Target
469586.description: The line between the hunted and the hunter becomes blurred when one man finds himself fighting a group that hunts other men for blood sport.

475898.title: Heathers
475898.description: When a snobbish high school clique threatens to ruin her reputation, a teenage girl teams up with a sociopath and plots to kill the cool kids.

477962.title: Set It Off
477962.description: Four African-American women in Los Angeles, all in dire financial circumstances, resort to robbing banks with action-packed, tragic consequences.

478517.title: The Beguiled
478517.description: Clint Eastwood is torn between his love and his life in this tense drama about a wounded Union soldier sheltered by a girls’ academy in the South during the height of the Civil War.

488977.title: Images
488977.description: A pregnant children’s author, who suspects her husband of having an affair, begins to unravel with memories of past trauma while vacationing in Ireland.

499404.title: The Texas Chain Saw Massacre
499404.description: After a run-in with a group of cannibals, a young woman and her friends are terrorized by Leatherface and his chainsaw  in this classic slasher.

499511.title: Man on Wire
499511.description: Philippe Petit, who walked an illegally rigged highwire between NYC’s twin towers in 1974, faces stupendous challenges for the sake of his daring art.

512448.title: New Jack City
512448.description: Two streetwise cops embark on the riskiest mission of their careers when they go undercover to bust a ruthless drug kingpin reigning over Harlem.

516368.title: Runaway Train
516368.description: Two prison escapees hop a train during the dead of winter, but their ride soon speeds out of control and freedom gets further out of reach.

526967.title: The Hills Have Eyes
526967.description: Terrifying original tale of a suburban family on a road trip to L.A who break down in the desert and get attacked by cannibals living in the hills.

526990.title: Re-Animator
526990.description: Cult horror-shocker about a medical student and his girlfriend who conduct outrageous experiments with dead tissue after a new student arrives.

543974.title: Tokyo Sonata
543974.description: When a father loses his high-paying job to outsourcing, he develops a ruse to keep his firing a secret and, in the process, tears his family apart.

545512.title: Blade II
545512.description: Blade, the vampire-human hybrid, joins forces with a highly-skilled team of vampires to vanquish a new race of super vampires out for Armageddon.

551307.title: Audition
551307.description: In his search for a new wife, a widowed TV producer stages a dating service to screen women and finds one who isn't quite as perfect as her audition.

555703.title: Coffy
555703.description: A tough and sexy vigilante uses her brains and guns to clean up the streets and get revenge after her sister falls victim to local drug dealers.

563040.title: Dead Presidents
563040.description: A Vietnam War veteran returns home and is drawn into a life of crime when he pulls off a daring armored car robbery with a group of fellow vets.

589088.title: Practical Magic
589088.description: Two magical New England sisters must outwit and overcome their family curse, which dooms the men they love to die in tragic circumstances.

589375.title: Tango & Cash
589375.description: A pair of rival LAPD cops become unlikely allies when both are framed and imprisoned on drug charges that force them in cahoots to clear their names.

593449.title: Dark Star
593449.description: Famed horror director John Carpenter’s early spaced-out odyssey about a crew in space starting to have hilarious mishaps after 20 years in orbit.

599629.title: Eyes Wide Shut
599629.description: Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman star as a married couple entangled in an intricate web of jealousy and sexual obsession in Stanley Kubrick's final cinematic offering.  At a Christmas party hosted by wealthy, unconventional Victor Ziegler (Sydney Pollack), provocative advances and innocent flirtations arouse suspicion as high-society physician Dr. William Harford (Cruise) and his sexy wife, Alice (Kidman) watch each other from a distance. Alone later, this seemingly perfect couple confront their intimate sexual fantasies--which don't include each other.  Caught between reality and illusion, jealousy and obsession, William struggles with his inner urges. Will he act on his erotic fantasies or keep them hidden deep inside? Sometimes a man can see more clearly with his Eyes Wide Shut.

599958.title: Maurice
599958.description: Set against the stifling conformity of pre-World War I English society, E.M. Forster's Maurice is a story of coming to terms with one's sexuality and identity in the face of disapproval and misunderstanding.

599997.title: Wedding Crashers
599997.description: Owen Wilson (Starsky & Hutch) and Vince Vaughn (Old School) star as John Beckwith and Jeremy Klein, two partying divorce attorneys--and committed womanizers--who have figured out a surefire way to meet women: they crash weddings. But the guys' happy-go-lucky lives change abruptly when John unexpectedly falls in love with a bridesmaid (Rachel McAdams - The Notebook). Things become even more complicated when the men discover that the object of John's affection is the daughter of the United States Secretary of the Treasury (Christopher Walken - Catch Me If You Can) in the engaging romantic comedy Wedding Crashers.

602060.title: The Shooting
602060.description: A mysterious woman, who keeps changing her story, persuades two cowboys to escort her on a trek across the desert and help her in a revenge scheme.

602292.title: Blade
602292.description: A vampire-human hybrid uses his advanced powers and an arsenal of weapons to do battle with the bloodsucking monsters who threaten the living.

604303.title: Daughters of the Dust
604303.description: At the dawn of the 20th century, a multi-generational family in the Gullah community on the Sea Islands off of South Carolina struggle to maintain their cultural heritage and folklore while contemplating a migration to the mainland.

607451.title: E.T. The Extra-Terrestrial
607451.description: A boy forms a special bond with a sweet and gifted alien from another planet. He tries to keep it a secret, but he needs help to keep the visitor safe.

607952.title: True Lies
607952.description: A deadly and talented spy for the government hides his dangerous day job from his family, but his secret heroics take a toll on his marriage.

610572.title: Goodfellas
610572.description: Based on a true story, a young man rises up the ranks of a mob family over several years, dabbling in drugs, heists and murders along the way.

617447.title: Pretty Woman
617447.description: Julia Roberts stars as a witty prostitute who charms a serious businessman, as the two unlikely lovers fall for each other over the course of a week.

633217.title: Joint Security Area
633217.description: “Squid Game” actor Lee Byung-hun stars in this military drama about a sergeant from South Korea accused of murdering a North Korean soldier.

637929.title: Carlito's Way
637929.description: In 1975 NYC, a rehabilitated ex-con drug dealer determined to stay clean is tempted back into the life by an array of lowlifes and former associates.

641207.title: The Hit
641207.description: After a decade in hiding for snitching on his mob associates, an ex-gangster is found in Spain and escorted on a wild ride to Paris for his execution.

643081.title: West Side Story
643081.description: This electrifying musical, winner of ten Academy Awards, including Best Picture, reimagines “Romeo and Juliet,” set during gang warfare in 1950s NYC.

645194.title: Deconstructing Harry
645194.description: A writer with a crummy and chauvinistic way of treating women remembers some extremely momentous times from his past to get over his writer’s block.

645491.title: Sweet and Lowdown
645491.description: Sean Penn stars as a gifted but mercurial jazz guitarist in the 1930s whose struggles with envy and mobsters are changed by his love for a mute woman.

652270.title: The Goonies
652270.description: A pair of brothers hope to save their house by following a treasure map and taking their friends along on a subterranean sea adventure.

664749.title: 10 Things I Hate About You
664749.description: On the first day at his new school, Cameron instantly falls for Bianca, the gorgeous girl of his dreams. The only problem? She isn't allowed to date.

664878.title: The Manchurian Candidate
664878.description: When a platoon of U.S. soldiers are captured during the Korean War, Major Bennett Marco discovers a diabolical plot involving enemy leaders.

665462.title: Apollo 13
665462.description: A routine space flight becomes a desperate battle of survival in this breathtaking and true-story of adventure, courage, and faith.

667228.title: Clockwatchers
667228.description: The relationship between four female temps all working for the same credit company is threatened with the arrival of a new permanent hire.

672301.title: The 40-Year-Old Virgin
672301.description: Nice guy Andy has lived his whole life without "doing it." Now, his misguided pals are helping him reverse his fortunes—and maybe even find true love.

672503.title: Death on the Nile
672503.description: While detective Hercule Poirot is enjoying some R&R on a luxurious cruise down the Nile River, a newlywed heiress is found murdered on board.

674418.title: Vampire's Kiss
674418.description: When a volatile literary agent encounters a neck-biter, he’s convinced that he’s turning into a vampire, and his behavior turns positively outrageous.

676725.title: Boyhood
676725.description: Richard Linklater's acclaimed hit, filmed over twelve years with the same cast, is a groundbreaking celebration of life, growing up, and parenting.

681750.title: Touching the Void
681750.description: An incredible account of tragedy and friendship, this film follows two men's thrilling and disastrous climb of the treacherous Siula Grande in Peru.

681782.title: Certified Copy
681782.description: A French antiques dealer meets a British writer and the two strangers fall in love while spending a romantic afternoon together in gorgeous Tuscany.

682797.title: Casper
682797.description: Seeing is believing in this adventure about a kind spirit in need of a friend and his ghostly uncles who want all “fleshies” out of their manor.

684141.title: Fish Tank
684141.description: A British 15-year-old aspiring dancer struggles with her mother’s immature ways, but finds herself drawn toward her mom’s boyfriend.

689650.title: The Pink Panther
689650.description: The bumbling Inspector Jacques Clouseau tries to catch an infamous jewel thief before he can steal a priceless diamond from a princess.

689652.title: In the Heat of the Night
689652.description: While traveling in the deep south, a black Philadelphian homicide detective becomes embroiled in a murder investigation.

689752.title: Drunken Master
689752.description: After a series of incidents, a mischievous yet righteous young man is sent into a brutal training program run by a master of drunken martial arts.

690311.title: The Reader
690311.description: In post-WWII Germany, a law student finds the older woman with whom he had an affair eight years ago, among Nazi prison guards being tried for murder.

694768.title: American Pie
694768.description: The stakes are high when four friends make the pact to lose their virginity by prom night in this romp about high school, band camp and apple pie.

698796.title: They Live
698796.description: After discovering a secret alien cabal to control the Earth with subliminal messages, one man goes on a crusade to awaken humanity from its spell.

707103.title: Blazing Saddles
707103.description: A corrupt governor will grant a reprieve to a convict under one condition: the condemned man agrees to serve as sheriff of a small Western town.

707299.title: Mighty Aphrodite
707299.description: Upon discovering his adopted son is a genius, a married writer becomes obsessed with finding the boy's birth mother, who turns out to be a sex worker.

715229.title: FernGully: The Last Rainforest
715229.description: The magical inhabitants of a rainforest must fight to save their home from the looming threat of a logging and a polluting force of destruction.

720955.title: Talk to Her
720955.description: The lives of the four characters will flow in all directions, past, present, and future, dragging them towards an unsuspected destiny.

723250.title: Bend It Like Beckham
723250.description: Despite the wishes of their traditional families, two young women from different walks of life aim for a career in professional soccer.

723254.title: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
723254.description: A distinguished young captain of the British Navy leads his crew on a mission to take a French vessel with a reputation for sinking British ships.

724377.title: Downfall
724377.description: Traudl Junge, the final secretary for Adolf Hitler, tells of the Nazi dictator's final days in his Berlin bunker at the end of World War II.

724777.title: Frances Ha
724777.description: A late-20s New York woman dreams of being a dancer but is only an apprentice for a dance company. As she reaches adulthood, she finds herself.

100000004.title: Gates of Heaven
100000004.description: Errol Morris' first documentary examines the devotions, emotions and obsessions felt by animal lovers amid the threat of a pet cemetery relocation.

100000037.title: In the Loop
100000037.description: A group of American and British operatives make attempts at damage control between the two nations while the U.S. thirsts for war in the Middle East.

100000089.title: Enter the Void
100000089.description: An American drug dealer living in Tokyo takes a psychedelic, acid trip-like journey into the afterlife when he’s killed in a deal gone bad.

100000098.title: The Thin Blue Line
100000098.description: The groundbreaking documentary exposing the cracks in the U.S. justice system and the manufacture of evidence that sent an innocent man to death row.

100000487.title: Ghostbusters II
100000487.description: The superstars of the supernatural reunite to battle an enormous underground river of slime that threatens New York City in this hilarious sequel.

100000784.title: Ghostbusters
100000784.description: A trio of failed university parapsychologists cash in on an uptick in New Yorkers’ paranormal complaints by setting up a ghost extermination service.

100001222.title: Rosewood
100001222.description: In this film inspired by true events, a mob attacks the Black residents of Rosewood, Florida after a false accusation incites racist violence.

100001367.title: Nobody Knows
100001367.description: Based on a true story, four young siblings are forced to rely solely on each other when they are left alone by their loving, yet immature mother.

100001368.title: Still Walking
100001368.description: Twelve years after the drowning death of the favorite son, a broken Japanese family performatively gathers for a graveside ritual to honor his memory.

100001409.title: The Big Red One
100001409.description: Deemed one of the most powerful films ever made about World War II, this story follows a squad of sharpshooters trying not to die in the Big Red One.

100001413.title: Matchstick Men
100001413.description: The streetwise teen daughter he never knew existed suddenly turns a neurotic con artist’s two-man team in small-time crime into a family business.

100001991.title: The Bourne Supremacy
100001991.description: Jason Bourne flees his hiding spot with an assassin at his heels, scouring the globe for answers about his forgotten past while dodging CIA agents.

100002047.title: Bring It On
100002047.description: With national championships fast approaching, the new cheerleading captain discovers that their winning routines were stolen from a rival squad.

100002112.title: Kill Bill: Vol. 1
100002112.description: After waking up from a four-year coma, a former assassin seeks revenge on the team of killers that betrayed her—and that she was once a part of.

100002113.title: Jackie Brown
100002113.description: Female flight attendant Jackie Brown becomes a key figure in a plot between the federal authorities and her street-tough arms dealer boss.

100002156.title: Men in Black
100002156.description: Tasked with policing extraterrestrial activities on Earth, two agents join forces to track down a dangerous alien intent upon galactic destruction.

100002159.title: Kill Bill: Vol. 2
100002159.description: The Bride continues her quest for revenge, fighting her way through a host of assassins in pursuit of a final showdown with the man who betrayed her.

100002337.title: Uncle Buck
100002337.description: Left in charge of his nephew and nieces during a family crisis, a fun-loving bachelor turns their suburban household upside-down with his wild ways.

100002340.title: High Plains Drifter
100002340.description: A gunslinging “Man with No Name” rides into the lawless Western settlement of Lago and makes a name for himself with a string of blazing battles.

100002343.title: Backdraft
100002343.description: Two clashing sibling firefighters with the Chicago Fire Department must set aside their differences to solve a puzzling series of arson attacks.

100002351.title: The Bourne Identity
100002351.description: An elite government agent is pulled out of a fishing boat with two bullets in his back and no memory before being forced on the run from assassins.

100003156.title: Back to the Future
100003156.description: Marty McFly is blasted to 1955 in a time machine created by Doc Brown and finds himself in a time-shattering situation that jeopardizes his future.

100003157.title: Back to the Future Part II
100003157.description: Marty McFly and Doc Brown launch themselves to the year 2015 to fine-tune the future and inadvertently disrupt the spacetime continuum.

100003275.title: Back to the Future Part III
100003275.description: Marty McFly travels to 1885 to rescue Doc Brown and put the past, present, and future on track so they can all return to where they belong.
